channel.title: Adding ::Players online list on a Solitude source. HELP
channel.description: I'm using a solitude source my friend gave to me i think it's a pi when i do ::online it shows how many people online, but how do i make it to where it shows a list of players online, anyone know? :s

item.title: Adding ::Players online list on a Solitude source. HELP
item.dc:creator: @matiasmunk matiasmunk
item.description:
@matiasmunk wrote:

All Time Low:

It doesn’t show the first person who’s online, leaves it blank.

Isn’t this obvious?

c.getPA().sendFrame126(Config.SERVER_NAME+" Online Players ("+PlayerHandler.getPlayerCount()+")", 8144);//Puts on like 8144 int line = 8146;//Puts on line 8146
What do you think? Perhaps change 8146 to 8145? Rofl.

item.description:
@dzeko wrote:

next time search…
took me 20 seconds.

if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("players")) { c.getPA().showInterface(8134); c.getPA().sendFrame126(Config.SERVER_NAME+" Online Players ("+PlayerHandler.getPlayerCount()+")", 8144); int line = 8146; for (Player p : PlayerHandler.players) { if (p != null) { Client o = (Client) p; c.getPA().sendFrame126(o.playerName, line); line++; } } }
